    {
      "id": "15e66f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "COLLEGE ADMISSIONS REQUIREMENTS FOR TRANSFER STUDENTS THIS MAJOR IS OFFERED BY THE COLLEGE OF LETTERS AND SCIENCE (L&amp;S) IMPORTANT information for students applying for admission to L&amp;S for the fall 2025 application cycle and beyond Completion of Essential Skills requirements (Reading &amp; Composition, Quantitative Reasoning, and Foreign Language) or Cal-GETC/IGETC will no longer be a requirement for admission; however, completion of either is strongly recommended prior to enrollment at UC Berkeley to ensure timely degree progress. More information on new polices is available on the L&amp;S Transfer Student Applicants website. By the end of the spring term preceding fall enrollment at Berkeley, you must complete : 1) The 7-course pattern (as found in the UC Transfer Admission Eligibility Courses Menu in ASSIST): · Two transferable courses in English composition; · One transferable course in mathematical concepts and quantitative reasoning; · Four transferable college courses chosen from at least two of the following subject areas: o arts and humanities o social and behavioral sciences o physical and biological sciences AND 2) Major Requirements : Follow the guidance on preparation for this major below. For more information on L&amp;S General Education requirements: For information on courses that will satisfy L&amp;S General Education (Essential Skills and Seven-Course Breadth) requirements from your community college complete the following steps: Go to \"Search below for articulation agreements: Major, department, and campus-specific general education agreements” Click on the down arrow to select: Academic Year, Institution: UC Berkeley , and Agreements with Other Institutions: (Your CA Community College). Click on “View Agreements”. Under “View Agreement by” select “ General Education/Breadth ”. Click on the “General Education/Breadth” radio button, then click on “View Agreement” Learn more from the UC Berkeley Office of Undergraduate Admission and specifically about transfer admission preparation. Review all available majors at UC Berkeley .",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong>COLLEGE ADMISSIONS REQUIREMENTS FOR TRANSFER STUDENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>THIS MAJOR IS OFFERED BY THE COLLEGE OF LETTERS AND SCIENCE (L&amp;S)</strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>IMPORTANT information for students applying for admission to L&amp;S for the fall 2025 application cycle and beyond</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Completion of Essential Skills requirements (Reading &amp; Composition, Quantitative Reasoning, and Foreign Language) or</p><p>Cal-GETC/IGETC will no longer be a requirement for admission; however, completion of either is<em> </em><strong><em>strongly recommended </em></strong></p><p>prior to enrollment at UC Berkeley to ensure timely degree progress. More information on new polices is available on</p><p>the L&amp;S <a href=\"https://ls.berkeley.edu/prospective-students/new-policies-transfer-student-applicants\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Transfer Student Applicants</a> website.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><strong>By the end of the spring term preceding fall enrollment at Berkeley, you must complete</strong>:&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>1)<a href=\"https://admission.universityofcalifornia.edu/admission-requirements/transfer-requirements/preparing-to-transfer/basic-requirements.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> The 7-course pattern</a>&nbsp;(as found in the UC Transfer Admission Eligibility Courses Menu in ASSIST):</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Two transferable courses in English composition;</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One transferable course in mathematical concepts and quantitative reasoning;</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Four transferable college courses chosen from at least two of the following subject areas:</p><p>o&nbsp;arts and humanities</p><p>o&nbsp;social and behavioral sciences</p><p>o&nbsp;physical and biological sciences</p><p><br></p><p>AND</p><p><br></p><p>2) <strong>Major Requirements</strong>:&nbsp;</p><p>Follow the guidance on preparation for this major below.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><strong>For more information on L&amp;S General Education requirements:</strong></p><p><br></p><p>For information on courses that will satisfy L&amp;S General Education (Essential Skills and </p><p>Seven-Course Breadth) requirements from your community college complete the following steps:</p><ol><li>Go to \"Search below for articulation agreements: Major, department, and campus-specific general education agreements”</li><li>Click on the down arrow to select: Academic Year, Institution: <strong>UC Berkeley</strong>, and Agreements with Other Institutions: (Your CA Community College).&nbsp;</li><li>Click on “View Agreements”.</li><li>Under “View Agreement by” select “<strong>General Education/Breadth</strong>”.&nbsp;</li><li>Click on the “General Education/Breadth” radio button, then click on “View Agreement”</li></ol><p><br></p><p><strong>Learn more from the UC Berkeley </strong><a href=\"http://admissions.berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Office of Undergraduate Admission</strong></a><strong> and specifically about </strong><a href=\"https://admissions.berkeley.edu/apply-to-berkeley/transfer-students/transfer-requirements/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>transfer admission</strong></a><strong> preparation.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Review all available majors at </strong><a href=\"https://undergraduate.catalog.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>UC Berkeley</strong></a>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "65db6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
